Rosey <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uclapperoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Clapperoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/02 2:34:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmmm</span><hr size=1> I'm a little skeptical, but honestly I don't think it will change skald's position in the realm.  Swords and Axes may be more viable weapons which makes me happy (I'm a sword weilder), although I will have some sympathy for hammer users if they become less effective.  Respec doesn't really affect higher level skalds unless they change weapon styles or the 50 spec BS ability.  The possible haste NPC will free skalds from taxi duties as I've said before.<br>
<br>
But then I always tend to fall on the side that Skalds need little work done on them at the moment (if the damage add bug is fixed, I'm totally happy).  If for some reason greater numbers of enemies are able to hit chain mail as a bonus that would be upsetting, but otherwise I don't see how much of this patch affects us at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/02 4:57:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> patch</span><hr size=1> (sorry, double post) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A> at: 7/26/02 5:00:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/26/02 4:59:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> patch</span><hr size=1> I agree, the patch doesn't affect us that much. No love, no nerf. <br>
<br>
The only problem I have with this patch is that it was supposed to solve the issues melee classes face in RvR, and it doesn't. Well, let's wait for F, G, H and Z, but I still doubt that further core change will be done. <br>
And that is important for us, because we are a melee class, playing in the melee realm. Midgard is not in a good shape in my server too (Guinevere), and, although there are exceptions and servers where Midgard does well, I begin too see a sad trend.<br>
<br>
1.51 was the magical patch. The magical realm, Hibernia, benefited a lot from this patch. A lot. And they now are on average at the top in the RvR war, since 1.51 went live. <br>
<br>
It's time for Midgard to receive a bit of &quot;love&quot;. And only a real melee patch that deals with true melee problems : crowd control, nukes for ridiculous damages, combination of the two (light spec in hibernia ...), not to mention PBAE and GTAE in static defense situation, rightly specced infiltrators that rape warriors in 1vs1 open combat without using stealth or critical strikes, etc ...<br>
<br>
And it is high time the heavy tank of the melee realm, the warrior, becomes something other than an incomplete/gimped hero or armsman.<br>
<br>
Don't take me wrong. I think the patch is good (hell, I am a sword user <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). It fixes and improves a lot of important issues : weapon/armor types imbalance, block/parry/bolt in RvR, respec, hasteners, bind points at portal gates ... <br>
<br>
But Myhic told us about a patch that would fix some RvR that prevents melee classes to enjoy the RvR experience and compete with other classes. For now, I don't feel the goal has been attained.<br>
<br>
Dargaard<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/02 12:41:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: patch</span><hr size=1> Thrust has a small penalty (or none) vs. scale. It's hammers that have a large penalty. Thrust infiltrators will continue to kill all tank classes.<br>
<br>
So far, this is a Midgard nerf and a Hib buff. Melee this time but who cares?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvivaxkithicor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vivax Kithicor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/02 2:09:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: patch</span><hr size=1> Of course my guild tested every class (in Midgard) for &quot;autotraining.&quot;<br>
<br>
We had been told my Mythic, and we also found out the hard way, that only &quot;pure tanks&quot; could autotrain.<br>
<br>
PALADINS can autotrain?!?!<br>
<br>
Just one more example of Albion being the pet realm.  I can buy it when Mythic says skalds and paladins come from the same base, so skalds should be compared with paladins instead of with bards and minstrels.  Ok, but then why don't SKALDS autotrain?<br>
<br>
No, as someone also on the outside casually watching in, this was not news which draws me back.<br>
<br>
-Scorn Hull, retired<br>
AGM of Reckoning<br>
Guinevere <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uvivaxkithicor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vivax Kithicor</A> at: 7/27/02 2:10:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukjeld.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/27/02 6:00:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: patch</span><hr size=1> I used to think, before 1.51 that Albion was Myhtic's pet realm. I don't think so anymore. Like us, Albion is going to be destroyed by the new Juggernaut, Hibernia. They created a monster with 1.51, and 1.52 patch as it is will reinforce the problem. Mix the whole overpowering mess with a realm battle hardened and wizened because they had been the underdog for so long ...<br>
<br>
So, I don't really believe you can accuse them of favoritism. It's just that they genuinely suck at balancing, making changes without imagining the repercussions. Too bad the mistakes aren't positive to Midgard ... As far as game balance is concerned, I seriously wish we could roll back to the situation a few months ago, before realm abilities in fact (which were the first exemple of Mythic completely loosing grasp on game balancing).<br>
<br>
Dargaard <p>---------
