<br>
Skalds (and the rest of Midgard) don't auto-train because we have the unique ability of being able to use a 2-handed sword and a 1-handed sword and utilize the same base skill for it. If a Paladin wants to use both a 1-hander and a 2-hander and switch off in various situations (like some skalds), they have to train both their primary weapon skill AND the 2-handed weapon skill.<br>
<br>
This is what Mythic has repeatedly said was the cause for the auto-training ... to compensate for that. Although, recently Sanya said it was to keep people from gimping themselves...So I guess people in Albion are more likely to place brain-dead spec templates than those in Midgard and they need the security? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
